<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: LONDON; THE CHUNNEL GALA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 This Friday, with major hoopla on both sides of the English Channel, the 
Chunnel -- the $15-billion Channel Tunnel -- will be inaugurated.Queen 
Elizabeth II will open a new terminal at Waterloo Station in London, while 
French President Francois Mitterrand will do the same at the Gare du Nord in 
Paris. 
</P>
<P>
 Both leaders will then take special trains to Calais in France for the formal 
ceremony and travel together through the tunnel to Folkestone on the British 
side. The tunnel trains will eventually carry freight, passengers and private 
cars. 
</P>
<P>
 Passenger service is expected to begin in a few months. It has been delayed by 
a shortage of rolling stock. 
</P>
