</P>
<P>
 The United States, despite boasting one of the world's largest armies, has 
made a relatively small contribution, in terms of soldiers, to United Nations 
peacekeeping missions. Thirty countries, many of them with armed forces just a 
fraction of the size of the U.S. military, had more personnel assigned to U.N. 
