<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County Sheriff Larry Carpenter and several deputies will don waiters' 
attire today to raise money for the family of a colleague who died of cancer 
last month. 
</P>
<P>
 The fund-raiser for Sheriff's Deputy John Russell Arthur will be held from 11 
a.m. to 10 p.m. today at Geppetto's restaurant at 868 Thousand Oaks Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 The price of all meals plus tips will be donated to Arthur's wife, Cheryl, and 
their four children, ages 8 through 14. Arthur, who worked at the Camarillo 
station, died of lymphoma April 15. He was 37. 
</P>
