 Detective Joe Braga said many deputies, as well as Carpenter, are expected to 
assist the restaurant's staff by taking orders, serving food and clearing 
tables. 
</P>
<P>
 Geppetto's is owned by Paul Burns, a former deputy who has hosted fund-raisers 
for law enforcement in the past.  
</P>
<P>
 For information about today's event, call 495-7456. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to dining at the restaurant, anyone interested in assisting 
Arthur's family may make a donation through the Bank of A. Levy. Checks or 
money orders should be sent to the Arthur Family Fund, care of Bank of A. Levy, 
5000 Santa Rosa Road, Camarillo, Calif. 93012. JULIE FIELDS 
