<P>
 Two people were hospitalized in serious condition Monday after a woman lost 
control of her van while driving across a bridge in Moorpark, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Fatin Hijaz, 20, of Moorpark was driving west on Tierra Rejado Road when she 
apparently lost control of the vehicle, crossed over to the eastbound lane, 
veered onto the sidewalk and hit two pedestrians, sheriff's deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
 Hijaz's vehicle then flew into the air and over an embankment before finally 
coming to rest at a nearby nursery, authorities said. 
</P>
