<HEADLINE>
<P>
CLAS ATTACKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The recent attacks against our state's CLAS examinations are a concerted 
effort orchestrated by national religious-right organizations such as the Eagle 
Forum, the Christian Coalition, the Rutherford Institute and Concerned Women 
for America. Although trying to disguise the attacks as local incidents, 
members of these organizations, with guidance from their national leaders, are 
waging a well-organized battle against every school district in the state of 
California.These are the same people who fight against sex education in high 
schools, work to censor reading material -- which they consider immoral -- from 
our children's schools, and oppose school breakfast programs and after-school 
care because they somehow devalue the family. 
</P>
<P>
 These organizations are very well-financed and, unfortunately, are succeeding 
at intimidating school districts into conformity with their very narrow 
viewpoint of how the world should be run. Our public schools enroll children 
from every nationality, race, religion and sexual orientation. The needs of all 
of these students should be met, not just the needs and desires of an extremely 
vocal, cash-rich minority. 
</P>
<P>
 I urge all school districts, especially the Simi Valley Unified School 
District, to consider the wants and needs of my children and the many other 
children who are not aligned with these organizations when making decisions 
concerning their education and future. It's time to start worrying about our 
children's education, not about the next election. 
</P>
<P>
 LINDA JORDAN-O'CONNOR 
</P>
<P>
 Simi Valley 
</P>
</TEXT>
