ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; RED CROSS CHAPTER AWARDS NOMINATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The local chapter of the American Red Cross is accepting nominations through 
May 10 for the second annual Clara Barton Spectrum Awards for Outstanding Women 
in Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
 Leaders of county businesses and organizations are encouraged to nominate 
women in the following categories: humanitarian service, health care, 
preservation of the environment and service by youth. 
</P>
<P>
 Nominations are also being accepted for the Group Award, honoring a business 
owned by a woman or a women's professional or volunteer group; and for the 
Elizabeth Dole Glass Ceiling Award, recognizing a woman who has overcome 
significant obstacles in improving her life or the lives of others. 
</P>
<P>
 The Clara Barton Spectrum Awards Luncheon, named in honor of the international 
founder of the Red Cross, will be June 21 at the Hyatt Regency Irvine. Tickets 
are $50 per person. 
</P>
<P>
 For luncheon reservations or information on nominations, call Kelley Schultz 
at (714) 835-5381, Ext. 248. 
