ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: WESTMINSTER; COUNCIL TO EVALUATE GRANT DISTRIBUTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council will conduct a study session today to determine how to 
distribute more than $166,000 in federal community development block grants to 
charities, nonprofit groups and city programs.  
</P>
<P>
 The grants from the Department of Housing and Urban Development are intended 
to fund public services for low-income families and senior citizens or to 
prevent slums and blighted neighborhoods. 
</P>
<P>
 At the 3 p.m. session, the council will consider requests from 22 local groups 
that have asked for a combined $287,000. Among the requests: the West Grove 
Pony Baseball League is asking for $2,000 and the Community Services and 
Recreation Department is seeking $50,000 for a gang prevention education 
program. The Boys and Girls Club of Westminster is requesting $40,000 and the 
Community Services Programs Inc. is seeking $35,000 for its programs for 
at-risk youths. BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</TEXT>
