ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: NEWPORT BEACH; POLICE SEEK MAN IN HOLDUPS AT TWO BARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police are looking for a man they believe is responsible for the armed robbery 
of a bar and the attempted robbery of another over the weekend as the bars were 
closing. 
</P>
<P>
 At 2:30 a.m. Saturday, the Classic Q Sports Bar, in the 4200 block of 
Martingale Way in Newport Beach, was robbed after the manager was tied up, 
according to Sgt. Andy Gonis.At 2:30 a.m. Sunday, a man hiding in a booth 
attempted to rob the Corona Cafe, in the 3200 block of East Coast Highway in 
Corona del Mar. The manager spotted the man, who was carrying a gun, and locked 
his office door, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 In both cases, a man about six feet tall wearing dark clothes and a ski mask 
brandished a gun and threatened employees while demanding money. Police believe 
the suspect patronizes the bars before the robberies. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone with information is asked to call Newport Beach detectives at (714) 
644-3717. 
</P>
