ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COSTA MESA NEWPORT BEACH; ESTANCIA PRINCIPAL TAKES YERMO 
JOB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Newport-Mesa Unified School District announced last week that Estancia 
High School Principal Frank Infusino has accepted an assistant superintendent 
job in Yermo. 
</P>
<P>
 Infusino will leave the district at the end of the school year for the 
2,800-student Silver Valley Unified School District, said Newport-Mesa Supt. 
Mac Bernd. 
</P>
<P>
 "He is really good," Bernd said. "I hate to lose him." 
</P>
<P>
 That means three of the four Newport-Mesa high schools will be looking for new 
principals before school starts next fall. The positions at Newport Harbor and 
Corona del Mar high schools are open as a result of a series of personnel 
changes announced recently. 
