retailer has agreed to demands that it modify a soon-to-be released proxy 
statement. 
</P>
<P>
 The shareholder, Kenneth Pavia, is general partner in Balboa Investment Group 
LP of Newport Beach, a limited partnership that controls 9.6% of the company's 
shares. 
</P>
<P>
 On Monday, Big O Tires of Englewood, Colo., agreed to his demands that it not 
count abstentions and broker non-votes when shareholders vote on whether to 
hire an investment banker who would explore ways to enhance shareholder value, 
including sale of the company.  
</P>
<P>
 "We think there are people out there willing to pay more than the present 
market price for Big O," Pavia said. "We're aware of some people who are 
interested." 
</P>
<P>
 The result of the proxy vote will be announced June 8 at the company's annual 
meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 Big O Tires owns or operates 354 stores nationwide, about 15 of them in Orange 
County. It has 34 stores in Canada. 
