Compiled by John O'Dell, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two New Entries: Mitsubishi, which just brought out a redesigned and revved-up 
Eclipse sports coupe, unveils the 3000 GT Spyder this fall. The car is a 
convertible version of Mitsubishi's 3000 GT sports car.But it's not just any 
old convertible. Not a shred of canvas anywhere. Instead, harking back to the 
1950s, when Ford tried the same thing with a full-size passenger coupe -- the 
