<HEADLINE>
<P>
GLENDALE / BURBANK FOCUS: GLENDALE; CITY OFFERS ALTERNATIVES TO KILLING PIGEONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JENNIFER OLDHAM 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 City officials are promoting education over euthanasia after a move by the 
City Council to trap and kill hundreds of pigeons ruffled residents' feathers.  
</P>
<P>
 The council will review several alternatives -- including an ordinance that 
would ban pigeon feeding -- during its afternoon meeting today. 
</P>
<P>
 The alternatives were drafted after a controversial council decision last 
month to trap and poison the prolific birds with carbon monoxide by putting 
them in a cloth sack and tying it to the tailpipe of a running car. 
</P>
<P>
 Removing the birds became necessary after a flock of pigeons 10,000 strong 
roosted in the downtown business district -- fouling awnings, sidewalks and 
ledges, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The city is the first in Los Angeles County to adopt such a sweeping measure, 
which prompted calls from animal rights activists around the country. JENNIFER 
OLDHAM 
</P>
</TEXT>
