REGIONAL EARNINGS: IHOP CORP. REPORTS PROFIT OF $2.26 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 IHOP Corp., the Glendale-based operator and franchiser of International House 
of Pancakes restaurants, said its first-quarter profit surged 57%, to $2.26 
million from $1.44 million a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 For the three months that ended March 31, IHOP's revenue, derived mainly from 
franchise fees and royalties, increased 9%, to $32.8 million from $30.2 million 
in the same quarter a year earlier. Systemwide, IHOP's restaurant sales grew 
17%, and same-store sales were up nearly 4% in the first quarter. The 
corporation opened 10 restaurants in the first quarter, and now has 579 
restaurants, most of them operated by franchisees. 
