 The company said its earnings for the quarter that ended Feb. 26 were hurt by 
a $300,000 charge for a recent management restructuring, plus price competition 
and product mix.Revenue in the latest quarter was up 2%, to $10.6 million from 
$10.4 million a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 For its fiscal year that ended Feb. 26, California Amplifier saw its profit 
halved, to $1.56 million from $3.05 million in its prior fiscal year. Its 
latest fiscal-year revenue, however, increased 14%, to $40.7 million from $35.8 
million. 
