REGIONAL ROUNDUP: CALNETICS PLANS TO ACQUIRE AGRICULTURAL PRODUCTS INC. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Calnetics Corp., a Chatsworth maker of molded plastic components for the 
building and plastics industries, says it has tentatively agreed to acquire 
Agricultural Products Inc. for about $4.4 million in cash and notes. 
</P>
<P>
 The deal, which is contingent upon reaching a definitive agreement and 
shareholder approval, is expected to be completed in May. Agricultural 
Products, a closely held private company based in Ontario, had sales of about 
$10 million in 1993. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
