hired as the basketball coach at Chicago State. . . . Irish jockey Declan 
Murphy, 27, was in critical condition after suffering severe head injuries when 
he was thrown from his horse, Arcot, then kicked by another horse in a race at 
Haydock Park in England. . . . Santa Monica College women's basketball coach 
Traci Waites resigned to accept an assistant coaching position at Arizona. . . 
. Paul Hornung, a former sports editor of the Columbus Dispatch, died of cancer 
at 78. . . . Former boxer Maurice (Lefty) Lachance, 72, died in Lewiston, Me. 
</P>
