<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; LAGUNA BEACH SWEEPS NO. 2 HUNTINGTON BEACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAN ARRITT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Laguna Beach came back from a disappointing loss last week to San Clemente, to 
sweep Huntington Beach, 15-8, 15-13, 15-3, in a nonleague boys' volleyball 
match Monday at Laguna Beach High School. 
</P>
<P>
 At stake was a potential higher seeding in the Southern Section playoffs, 
scheduled to start May 13, and the fourth-ranked Artists (12-1) put in their 
bid with a dominant performance. 
</P>
<P>
 Junior outside hitter Dan Styles led Laguna Beach with 20 kills and 6-foot-9 
middle blocker Szilard Kovacs solidified the defense with five blocks. 
</P>
<P>
 "We got a tremendous team effort from everyone tonight," Artist Coach Michael 
Soylular said. "Our serving was good and we just played like a team." 
</P>
<P>
 The second-ranked Oilers (13-2) rallied only once, when they went on an 8-1 
run in the second game to catch Laguna Beach, 12-12. However, the Artists 
regrouped and won the game when Nick Ziegler's spike found the net. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach pounded away at the Oilers in the third game and led, 10-3, when 
Huntington Beach Coach Rocky Ciarelli was ejected after disputing a call. 
</P>
<P>
 "I hate to see Rocky get ejected in such a good match," Soylular said. "He's a 
good friend of mine." DAN ARRITT 
</P>
</TEXT>
