<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY/VENTURA DIGEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF FLETCHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Frank Cantu will return to Alemany High as the school's baseball coach, 
succeeding Jim Ozella, who announced earlier this year that he will resign at 
the end of the season. 
</P>
<P>
 Cantu, 40, coached at Alemany for five years in the 1980s but left the school 
to become the principal at St. Didacus Elementary School in Sylmar. 
</P>
<P>
 After two years as the junior varsity coach, he led the varsity for three 
seasons. In 1981 he coached the team into the playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 Cantu will remain as principal at St. Didacus. Basketball 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura College's Brandon Jessie, the state junior college basketball player 
of the year, has signed a letter of intent to play at Utah, Pirate Coach Philip 
Mathews said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Jessie, a 6-foot-5 1/2 forward, took trips to Utah, Georgetown, Arizona State 
and Nevada Las Vegas. Mathews said Jessie might have been swayed because Utah 
Coach Rick Majerus came to Ventura to visit him. 
</P>
<P>
 Mathews said Duke and UCLA were among the schools that recruited Jessie, but 
they dropped out. 
</P>
<P>
 Jessie, who averaged 22 points and 11 rebounds per game last year for the 
Pirates, is a two-time All-Western State Conference selection. JEFF FLETCHER 
</P>
</TEXT>
