<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY/VENTURA DIGEST: MISCELLANY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Andy Gavel, the boys' basketball coach at Paraclete High for the past 12 
years, has been hired as athletic director at Crespi High. 
</P>
<P>
 Gavel says he will not coach Crespi's basketball team next season but might 
serve as an assistant.Gavel replaces Paul Muff, who died suddenly in January. 
He was 46. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's a good thing for me to get away from coaching for a year," he said. "I 
feel apprehensive about the new situation, yet really excited." Softball 
</P>
<P>
 Valley College will reinstate its softball program next season after a 
five-year absence, Athletic Director Chuck Ferrero announced Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Ferrero said the program was dropped "for a variety of reasons" after the 1989 
season but that he has intended to bring it back since becoming athletic 
director four years ago. 
</P>
<P>
 No coach has been selected. 
</P>
